==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*firtan-'', from Indo-European ''*perd-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old High German [[ferzan]] (German [[furzen]]), Old Norse [[freta]] (Swedish [[fjårta]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[πέρδομαι]], Russian [[пердеть]], Lithuanian [[persti|pérsti]], Welsh [[rhech]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'feoɹtan/

===Verb===
'''feortan'''
# to [[fart]]

